			<div class="c-issue-toc__article-collapse collapse" id="collapseSummary753">
				<div class="c-issue-toc__article-collapse-inner">
					<p>The article attempts to map key aspects of internet critique in the contexts of its relation to communication capitalism. It does so however from the perspective of visual studies. In his analysis of YouTube, the author questions assumptions of the secondary nature of visual data in the internet. The article is a preliminary mapping of the field and aims to develop research questions that need to be answered from the perspective of visual studies.</p>
